 
TASK 1: OpenShift Installation (required) 
1.1 Generate discovery ISO via Red Hat Assisted Installer 
1.2 Configure Intersight Virtual Media policy with ISO URL 
1.3 Boot blades and assign roles (3 master/worker, 2 GPU worker) 
1.4 Complete OpenShift installation and cluster bootstrap 
1.5 Validate all nodes Ready and cluster operators healthy 
1.6 Configure kubeadmin credentials and oc CLI access 
1.7 Configure NTP sync across all nodes 
 
---
 
TASK 2: Dell GPU Server Setup (required) 
2.1 Install RHEL OS on Dell GPU server 
2.2 Install NVIDIA GPU drivers 
2.3 Install CUDA toolkit 
2.4 Validate GPU detection (nvidia-smi) 
2.5 Join Dell server to OpenShift as worker node (if applicable) 
 
---
 
TASK 3: Storage Networking â€“ MachineConfig (required) 
3.1 Create MachineConfigs for VLAN subinterfaces on storage interfaces 
3.2 Configure infra/app VLANs for dev/test/prod 
3.3 Assign IPs and set MTU 9000 
3.4 Validate connectivity and jumbo frames to NetApp LIFs 
 
---
 
TASK 4: NetApp Trident CSI (required) 
4.1 Install Trident operator 
4.2 Create Trident backends for infra and app SVMs (dev/test/prod) 
4.3 Create StorageClasses per environment 
4.4 Validate PVC creation and pod mounts 
4.5 Validate read/write access to NetApp 
 
---
 
TASK 5: Internal Image Registry (required) 
5.1 Enable OpenShift internal registry 
5.2 Back registry storage with NetApp via Trident 
5.3 Validate image push/pull 
5.4 Configure image pull secrets 
 
---
 
TASK 6: Ingress and Load Balancing (required) 
6.1 Deploy MetalLB or configure F5 integration 
6.2 Define IP pools and ingress configuration 
6.3 Configure DNS wildcard records 
6.4 Configure TLS certificates 
6.5 Validate external access 
 
---
 
TASK 7: Authentication and RBAC (required) 
7.1 Configure identity provider 
7.2 Define RBAC for admin, dev, and ops roles 
7.3 Create dev/test/prod namespaces 
7.4 Apply quotas, limits, and network policies 
 
---
 
TASK 8: GPU Operator and Scheduling (required) 
8.1 Install Node Feature Discovery 
8.2 Install NVIDIA GPU Operator 
8.3 Configure GPU scheduling (basic time-slicing or default mode) 
8.4 Apply taints/tolerations for GPU nodes 
8.5 Validate GPU access from pods 
 
---
 
TASK 9: GitOps (required) 
9.1 Install OpenShift GitOps (ArgoCD) 
9.2 Configure ArgoCD and RBAC 
9.3 Define repository structure (platform vs application) 
9.4 Bootstrap cluster configuration via GitOps 
9.5 Validate sync and rollback 
 
---
 
TASK 10: Backup and Disaster Recovery (required) 
10.1 Install Velero or OADP 
10.2 Configure backup storage location 
10.3 Define backup schedules for namespaces and PVs 
10.4 Configure etcd backup automation 
10.5 Test restore of a sample namespace 
 
---
 
TASK 11: End-to-End Validation (required) 
11.1 Deploy sample AI workload using GPU + NetApp storage 
11.2 Validate deployment via GitOps 
11.3 Validate basic isolation between dev/test/prod 
11.4 Validate backup and restore of workload 
 
---
 
TASK 12: Monitoring and Alerting (future / add-on) 
12.1 Configure persistent storage for monitoring 
12.2 Define retention policies 
12.3 Create custom alert rules 
12.4 Create dashboards 
 
---
 
TASK 13: Logging (future / add-on) 
13.1 Deploy logging stack 
13.2 Configure persistent storage 
13.3 Define retention policies 
13.4 Configure log forwarding if needed 
